<i>Please scan your item.</i>

03:05.375 --> 03:06.417
You're very boring.

03:07.125 --> 03:08.375
<i>Please scan your item.</i>

03:08.457 --> 03:09.500
Yeah, right.

03:15.792 --> 03:17.042
Sir!

03:17.707 --> 03:18.707
Sir?

03:18.792 --> 03:21.457
Sir, I need you to stop. Hey!

03:21.540 --> 03:23.415
Whoa! Oh, hey!

03:24.625 --> 03:26.000
Sir, let me help you.

03:26.084 --> 03:28.415
- You hurt my leg! Get away!
- Come on, sir.

03:28.500 --> 03:30.457
Get out of the way!
I'm a senior citizen!

03:30.540 --> 03:32.375
- Get out of here!
- I know judo.

03:33.792 --> 03:35.125
Leave that
poor man alone!

03:36.167 --> 03:38.209
- Whoa!
- Your pharmacy stinks!

03:41.042 --> 03:42.582
- You're ageist!
- Oh, I see.

03:42.665 --> 03:44.167
Y'all want to bring it on.

03:44.250 --> 03:45.707
You want to bring it on?

03:46.582 --> 03:48.167
- Treat us with respect!
- Oh!

03:49.415 --> 03:51.415
That's all you got?

03:51.500 --> 03:53.250
Now, that hurt.

03:58.167 --> 03:59.625
Hey, there's my girl.

03:59.707 --> 04:01.250
You didn't have to come
all this way.

04:01.334 --> 04:02.334
I told you I was fine.

04:02.415 --> 04:03.832
What happened
to the mailbox?

04:05.082 --> 04:07.167
Oh, that.
Some idiot took it out.

04:13.167 --> 04:14.167
Oh, crap.

04:14.917 --> 04:16.791
Dad, you're driving again,
aren't you?

04:17.000 --> 04:18.665
You lost your license,
remember?

04:18.750 --> 04:20.832
No, I didn't lose it.
I forgot to renew it.

04:20.916 --> 04:23.375
So now I have to
retake the test again, which is idiotic

04:23.457 --> 04:25.292
because I've been driving
for over 50 years.

04:25.375 --> 04:27.292
I mean, what am I supposed to do,
starve to death?

04:27.375 --> 04:28.375
I'm coming in.

04:34.167 --> 04:36.167
This can't keep happening.

04:36.665 --> 04:39.084
Don't worry, I'm never going back
to that damn store again.

04:39.167 --> 04:40.415
No, I mean the part about,

04:40.500 --> 04:42.292
I have to leave
the dealership early,

04:42.375 --> 04:44.625
drive two hours each way
just to check on you.

04:44.707 --> 04:46.042
I didn't ask you to come!

04:46.375 --> 04:48.457
No, you didn't!
The police did.

04:48.707 --> 04:51.084
Dad, I want to come.
I want to be there for you.

04:51.917 --> 04:52.917
But maybe this is

04:53.125 --> 04:55.500
now the time
that we have to consider...

04:55.582 --> 04:57.540
No. I am not moving.

04:57.625 --> 04:59.167
I built this house,

04:59.250 --> 05:01.458
I'm gonna die in this house,
and that's it.

05:01.540 --> 05:03.500
And you're not
putting me in a home.

05:05.125 --> 05:07.750
- What if it were our home?
- What are you talking about?

05:07.833 --> 05:09.833
Fish and relatives
stink after three days.

05:09.916 --> 05:12.166
That's a horrible idea.
We'll kill each other.

05:12.375 --> 05:13.791
It ain't working.
No, sorry.

05:13.875 --> 05:14.875
Dad...

05:21.042 --> 05:22.415
I miss her, too.

05:22.917 --> 05:24.540
And, and that's
not gonna change

05:24.625 --> 05:27.667
by moving me out of my house
and sticking me in yours.

05:30.250 --> 05:31.290
Oh, God.

05:34.707 --> 05:37.500
Well, maybe we could
miss her together.

05:37.582 --> 05:38.917
Yeah, maybe.

05:39.000 --> 05:40.707
But you don't have the room
in your house anyway.

05:40.792 --> 05:42.167
Where would you
even put me?

05:42.375 --> 05:44.415
The attic? No way!

05:44.500 --> 05:47.000
Come on, buddy,
don't make this harder than it already is.

05:47.084 --> 05:48.290
It's the only choice.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.290
Ooh!

05:51.415 --> 05:54.832
Dad, if it's the only choice,
then it isn't a choice at all.

05:55.167 --> 05:58.332
'Cause a choice means you get to pick
between at least two things.

05:58.415 --> 05:59.540
And this is one thing.

05:59.625 --> 06:03.375
Unless the other thing is I get to sleep
in the yard and get eaten by a bear.

06:03.458 --> 06:04.833
Don't be so dramatic, Peter.

06:05.000 --> 06:07.084
Besides, your sisters
already share a room.

06:07.166 --> 06:09.084
Yeah, well,
Sarah told me you said that.

06:09.250 --> 06:10.415
No, I know
she exaggerates, but...

06:10.500 --> 06:12.250
<i>Christmastime is here</i>

06:12.333 --> 06:13.375
<i>Happiness and cheer...</i>

06:13.458 --> 06:14.916
No, you stop.
Hold on. Shh!

06:16.167 --> 06:17.209
Shh!

06:17.582 --> 06:18.917
Shh!

06:19.000 --> 06:20.250
Shh!

06:20.332 --> 06:21.750
- Shh!
- Shh!

06:21.832 --> 06:23.707
- Shh! Shh!
- Shh! Shh!

06:23.792 --> 06:25.000
- Shh!
- Shh!

06:25.625 --> 06:27.250
- Shh!
- Shh!

06:27.332 --> 06:28.959
- Shh!
- Shh! Shh!

06:29.042 --> 06:30.042
Shh!

06:31.167 --> 06:32.167
Hey, what's up?

06:32.457 --> 06:33.540
Shh!

06:33.625 --> 06:35.540
Plus, the attic
doesn't have a bathroom.

06:35.625 --> 06:37.959
<i>And Grandpa
can't do all those stairs.</i>

06:38.415 --> 06:41.540
And the basement...
is the basement.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.000
What?

06:46.415 --> 06:47.415
My Jordans.

06:47.500 --> 06:49.000
I just put in fresh laces.

06:49.084 --> 06:51.832
Hey, Peter.
Do you need help moving upstairs?

06:51.917 --> 06:53.542
Get out!
It's still my room!

06:54.207 --> 06:55.415
- Hmm.
- Not for long.

06:56.042 --> 06:58.500
Go away!
Go, go, go.

06:59.832 --> 07:02.666
Look, Peter,
I know this is not ideal,

07:02.750 --> 07:04.415
but we're a family,

07:04.500 --> 07:06.750
and you have to make
sacrifices for each other.

07:06.833 --> 07:08.583
Sometimes
very big sacrifices.

07:14.250 --> 07:18.167
Look, sweetheart,
the attic is bigger than this room.

07:18.250 --> 07:20.500
Once you move in,
then that will be your room.

07:20.582 --> 07:21.625
No, it won't.

07:21.875 --> 07:23.375
It'll be the attic,

07:23.457 --> 07:25.207
where you put stuff
and forget it,

07:25.290 --> 07:26.625
just like our old TV,

07:26.832 --> 07:28.834
or the exercise bike
that Dad used once.

07:29.457 --> 07:32.625
- True.
- I exercise. What?

07:33.375 --> 07:35.582
Look, think about it
as a fresh new start.

07:35.875 --> 07:37.667
All right?
We'll dust everything off,

07:37.750 --> 07:39.625
put some new paint up
everywhere.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.457
Give you a chance to...
clean out your turtle tank.

07:42.582 --> 07:44.375
- Huh?
- They like it like that.

07:44.959 --> 07:46.332
Gives them privacy.

07:46.707 --> 07:48.332
Does this still fit you, sweetie?

07:49.125 --> 07:50.125
Yes.

07:53.959 --> 07:55.042
Grandpa!

07:55.959 --> 07:58.084
<i>Grandpa's here, Grandpa's here</i>

07:58.290 --> 07:59.707
<i>Grandpa all the way</i>

07:59.792 --> 08:05.084
<i>Oh, what fun it is to have
a Grandpa come and stay, hey</i>

08:05.333 --> 08:06.875
Hey! Now, remember,

08:06.959 --> 08:08.916
we don't want to overwhelm
Grandpa, okay?

08:09.000 --> 08:10.541
So let's let him
get settled in.

08:10.625 --> 08:13.583
There'll be plenty of time
to talk to him tonight at dinner. Okay?

08:13.666 --> 08:14.750
Oh, I'm not gonna be here.

08:14.834 --> 08:17.000
- What?
- What? I'm studying with Russell.

08:17.084 --> 08:19.332
"Studying" still means studying, right?

08:19.415 --> 08:21.042
It's not slang
for something else?

08:21.125 --> 08:23.082
No, Dad, "studying"
still means studying.

08:23.250 --> 08:24.959
And I already
cleared it with Mom.

08:27.084 --> 08:29.792
- Grandpa!
- Jenny!

08:29.874 --> 08:31.165
Don't body-slam.

08:34.792 --> 08:37.164
- Hi, Grandpa.
- Hello, sweetheart.

08:39.875 --> 08:41.207
- Ed.
- Artie.

08:44.500 --> 08:45.582
Where's your brother?

08:46.457 --> 08:47.875
Peter?

08:47.959 --> 08:48.959
Peter!

08:49.457 --> 08:50.500
Peter?

08:52.457 --> 08:54.582
Kids, let's help, uh,
Grandpa get his bags.

08:54.667 --> 08:56.290
- Okay. I got this.
- I got it.

08:56.375 --> 08:58.750
Okay. It just...
It's right over here.

09:04.750 --> 09:06.250
You know,
he called me Artie again.

09:06.332 --> 09:07.917
Please, Arthur.

09:08.166 --> 09:09.582
This isn't easy for him.

09:17.750 --> 09:18.917
Hey, Grandpa.

09:19.000 --> 09:23.207
Hey! There he is!
Look at you.

09:24.082 --> 09:26.875
Look at you.
You're sprouting up like a weed.

09:27.833 --> 09:29.917
Oh. Nice sneakers.

09:30.000 --> 09:32.207
Thanks.
How do you like your room?

09:32.917 --> 09:34.000
It looks nice.

09:34.082 --> 09:35.582
Yeah, that's 'cause it is nice.

09:35.875 --> 09:37.917
Easily the nicest room
in the house.

09:38.500 --> 09:39.500
Well, I know, kid.

09:39.582 --> 09:41.667
Look, I didn't want it
to be this way, either.

09:42.875 --> 09:45.332
Sometimes you have to make
sacrifices in a family.

09:45.500 --> 09:47.082
That's true.
You're right.

09:48.125 --> 09:49.917
Sometimes you don't even
get a vote.

09:50.500 --> 09:51.582
That makes two of us.

09:52.875 --> 09:54.375
Careful with
these floorboards.

09:54.917 --> 09:55.917
They're not very level.

09:56.000 --> 09:57.625
I'll remember that.
Thanks, kiddo.

10:01.542 --> 10:02.917
Talk to you later,
Grandpa.

10:06.875 --> 10:08.625
Come visit me
in the attic anytime.

10:09.082 --> 10:11.291
It's the creepy place
with all the spiders and mice.

10:11.375 --> 10:13.417
- Peter!
- I wasn't!

10:33.709 --> 10:34.750
Here we are.

10:39.542 --> 10:40.750
You were robbed, bro.

10:40.834 --> 10:42.457
No. I was invaded.

10:42.542 --> 10:45.457
The worst part is
I'm not even allowed to complain about it.

10:45.542 --> 10:47.709
Seems like you've been
complaining an awful lot, P.

10:47.792 --> 10:49.332
I mean at home,
'cause he's old

10:49.417 --> 10:50.792
and we all love him
and stuff.

10:50.875 --> 10:53.625
Dude, come on, you can't allow
the enemy to invade your base.

10:53.709 --> 10:56.165
You got to fight back
and stick up for your rights.

10:56.250 --> 10:57.332
I don't have rights.

10:57.417 --> 11:00.292
Everyone has rights.
They're in, uh...

11:00.375 --> 11:02.292
Uh, alien-something.

11:02.375 --> 11:04.457
They have to allow you
to pursue happiness.

11:04.542 --> 11:05.792
It's in the Constitution.

11:05.875 --> 11:08.457
Yeah. Well, that would
be great if I lived in North America,

11:08.542 --> 11:10.833
but it turns out that
153 Burlington Avenue

11:10.917 --> 11:13.250
- is actually in North Korea.
- Whoa!

11:14.166 --> 11:16.750
Did your parents know that
when they bought the house?

11:20.125 --> 11:21.166
What?

11:22.166 --> 11:23.875
I wouldn't put up
with this, Petes.

11:23.957 --> 11:26.667
I'd demand my room back,
or else it's war.

11:26.750 --> 11:28.582
What do you mean,
"or else it's war"?

11:28.667 --> 11:30.542
You want him
to attack his grandfather?

11:30.917 --> 11:32.500
Sneak attack, Emma.

11:32.582 --> 11:35.000
See, he can't fight him
the normal way,

11:35.082 --> 11:38.207
because his grandfather has
strength, size and experience,

11:38.375 --> 11:41.165
whereas Peter
is just weak, small and dumb.

11:41.709 --> 11:42.915
You're a bad friend.

11:43.875 --> 11:45.207
Hi, Steven.

11:46.417 --> 11:49.875
Mom says don't forget to wear your
sandals when you shower in gym class.

11:51.834 --> 11:53.625
Not cool, Lisa.

11:53.709 --> 11:57.165
My brother has that toe fungus thing.
It's totally gross.

11:57.250 --> 12:00.583
- And contagious.
- Contagious?

12:01.750 --> 12:05.000
- Gross.
- It's only on six of my toes.

12:05.082 --> 12:07.125
That's a lot of toe, bro.

12:10.375 --> 12:13.542
<i>When you leave me</i>

12:13.957 --> 12:17.082
<i>My world's not alive</i>

12:17.957 --> 12:20.833
<i>You'll be in my days
and nights...</i>

12:22.542 --> 12:25.125
- Hi, Grandpa.
- Hi, sweetheart.

12:25.207 --> 12:26.542
Do you want
to play a game?

12:26.792 --> 12:29.375
I have <i>Reindeer Run.</i>

12:29.457 --> 12:32.584
I have <i>Santa's World.</i>

12:32.667 --> 12:35.542
I have
<i>1-2-3 Christmas Tree.</i>

12:35.625 --> 12:37.500
Well, maybe,
but not right now, okay?

12:43.082 --> 12:44.332
Want to watch a movie?

12:44.417 --> 12:47.207
I have <i>Frosty the Snowman.</i>

12:47.292 --> 12:49.500
I don't think so,
okay, sweetheart?

12:50.082 --> 12:51.792
- Maybe tomorrow?
- Okay.

12:58.250 --> 12:59.957
What's wrong with Grandpa?

13:00.041 --> 13:02.000
Why? What happened?

13:02.417 --> 13:04.041
He doesn't want
to do anything.

13:04.125 --> 13:07.082
He just stares out the window,
but there's nothing there

13:07.167 --> 13:10.041
except that dead tree
that Daddy says he's gonna cut down.

13:10.125 --> 13:12.082
But you won't let him
use the chain saw.

13:12.167 --> 13:15.542
Daddy can use a chain saw
any time he wants, honey. Okay?

13:16.000 --> 13:20.125
He just chooses to wait
until Mommy says it's okay.

13:21.250 --> 13:25.041
Grandpa will be all right.
He's just tired

13:25.125 --> 13:26.708
and thinking a lot
about Grandma.

13:27.041 --> 13:28.957
- He'll be okay.
- Okay.

13:42.332 --> 13:43.957
Get away from me!

13:54.915 --> 13:56.082
I hate my life.

14:19.875 --> 14:21.750
Oh, come on.

14:24.832 --> 14:26.000
Ow!

14:45.500 --> 14:46.957
"Declaration of War.

14:47.417 --> 14:50.250
"When in the course
of human events

14:50.832 --> 14:52.542
<i>"one person steals</i>

14:53.375 --> 14:55.292
<i>"another person's bedroom,</i>

14:55.375 --> 14:57.750
<i>"there is no other choice
but war.</i>

15:00.082 --> 15:03.875
"You have 24 hours
to give me back what is mine

15:03.957 --> 15:05.957
"or face the consequences.

15:06.667 --> 15:08.042
"Secret Warrior."

15:12.707 --> 15:13.750
Nice handwriting.

15:16.583 --> 15:17.707
It's not bad.
It's just...

15:17.791 --> 15:19.791
You know,
it's an adjustment, so...

15:21.583 --> 15:23.207
- Yeah.
- Who are you talking to?

15:23.292 --> 15:25.625
What? It's Jerry.
I'm just... I'm on the phone.

15:26.042 --> 15:27.082
No, I would love to.

15:27.167 --> 15:30.167
I would love to, but I can't.
I'm sort of stuck here. Yeah.

15:30.250 --> 15:32.750
- Hi, Jerry. It's Sally.
- Hey!

15:33.082 --> 15:34.957
- He's not stuck.
- What are you doing?

15:35.042 --> 15:37.832
Yeah, I'll bring him over
on my way to work. See you soon.

15:38.707 --> 15:39.707
Bye, Jerry.

15:39.790 --> 15:42.832
So, now you're setting me up
on playdates?

15:42.915 --> 15:45.332
Gonna pack me a lunch,
maybe put a note in it?

15:45.417 --> 15:47.750
You want a note?
You might not like what it says.

15:47.832 --> 15:50.000
I'll see him another time.
I'm not up to it.

15:50.082 --> 15:51.832
You haven't seen
Jerry in ages.

15:52.000 --> 15:53.665
Now you live close.
It'll be nice.

15:53.750 --> 15:56.207
I can't, I don't want to,
and I've got stuff to do.

15:56.292 --> 15:58.207
I have to take care
of the light switch

15:58.292 --> 16:02.042
in my room now,
'cause Artie put it in backwards. You did.

16:02.791 --> 16:04.500
Eat up.
We leave in 15 minutes.

16:04.707 --> 16:06.082
Yes, Mom.

16:06.375 --> 16:08.666
How's it going, Grandpa?
Sleep okay?

16:08.916 --> 16:10.292
Like a log, Petey.
Thanks.

16:11.042 --> 16:13.957
- Don't you guys get the paper around here?
- Yeah, we do.

16:16.375 --> 16:19.207
- Here it is.
- Oh, I can't read this.

16:19.625 --> 16:23.042
- Just make it bigger, see?
- Oh, yeah.

16:25.000 --> 16:26.707
- Jen...
- How does she survive?

16:26.791 --> 16:28.875
- She doesn't eat anything.
- I don't know.

16:28.957 --> 16:30.500
- Don't be late, Peter.
- Okay.

16:31.417 --> 16:33.500
So, no nightmares?

16:33.584 --> 16:35.292
- Me? No.
- Insomnia?

16:35.375 --> 16:37.292
Now it's like eight words
on the whole screen.

16:37.375 --> 16:38.915
You don't want
to talk about anything?

16:39.000 --> 16:40.500
I just made
the whole thing disappear.

16:40.584 --> 16:43.125
- I don't know what I did just now.
- Peter, let's go!

16:43.207 --> 16:45.000
Okay, well, if you want
to talk about

16:45.082 --> 16:46.750
something later on,
we can do that.

16:52.167 --> 16:53.250
Okay, have a good day.

16:58.832 --> 16:59.999
He didn't react at all?

17:00.082 --> 17:01.791
Not a word.
What's his game?

17:02.167 --> 17:03.457
What's yours, Pete?

17:03.666 --> 17:04.875
I mean, come on,

17:05.207 --> 17:06.958
you don't start a war
with a note.

17:07.040 --> 17:08.790
Maybe he didn't
actually read it.

17:08.958 --> 17:09.958
He read it.

17:10.165 --> 17:11.833
It was on his desk, unfolded.

17:11.915 --> 17:14.415
Maybe he forgot what he read.
Old people do that.

17:14.500 --> 17:16.040
You do that, Steve.

17:23.833 --> 17:24.833
Oops.

17:25.000 --> 17:26.790
That happened.

17:30.541 --> 17:33.459
But the point is you've already
blown the element of surprise.

17:33.541 --> 17:35.125
You've got to attack immediately.

17:35.208 --> 17:37.000
Um, there's chili in your backpack.

17:37.083 --> 17:38.750
- He knows.
- Yeah.

17:40.208 --> 17:42.334
- Hi, Steven.
- Oh, God, no.

17:42.416 --> 17:44.958
You left your retainer
in the back seat of Mom's car.

17:46.166 --> 17:48.375
I think a Snickers
got mashed up in it.

17:48.459 --> 17:51.000
- Ugh.
- At least I hope that's a Snickers.

17:52.875 --> 17:53.875
See you at dinner.

17:59.625 --> 18:01.041
We're good,
it's a Snickers.

18:02.958 --> 18:06.625
- Coming along, Arthur?
- Not bad. If you like big boxes.

18:08.000 --> 18:09.750
Big boxes
built this company.

18:11.540 --> 18:13.209
Yes. Yes, they did.

18:14.209 --> 18:16.125
You sure that's
the Walmart footprint?

18:17.125 --> 18:18.166
"Walmart"?

18:18.625 --> 18:20.166
Thought this was for Kmart.

18:20.375 --> 18:21.500
It's Walmart.

18:21.583 --> 18:24.459
Oh, man. I'm sorry.

18:24.540 --> 18:27.083
I, uh, got a lot
on my mind these days.

18:27.166 --> 18:29.375
My father-in-law
just moved in with us, so...

18:30.750 --> 18:33.875
I don't know.
I feel like he judges me.

18:35.291 --> 18:38.833
He thinks I work for some
soul-sucking corporate firm

18:39.000 --> 18:41.916
that has no interest
in the cares or worries of its...

18:45.750 --> 18:46.790
Its employees.

18:52.540 --> 18:53.958
Have a good time.

18:54.209 --> 18:55.665
So I'm just gonna walk home?

18:56.334 --> 18:57.958
Well, you can if you want.

18:59.334 --> 19:00.459
Or you can use this.

19:03.790 --> 19:05.083
I already have a phone.

19:05.166 --> 19:07.625
That's not a phone.
I don't even know what that is.

19:09.500 --> 19:10.500
Just take it.

19:14.459 --> 19:17.083
Okay, now, this is
a car service called Lyft.

19:17.166 --> 19:19.166
You want to go home,
you just swipe that,

19:19.250 --> 19:21.708
somebody comes to get you.
You don't need any cash.

19:21.791 --> 19:24.375
- You don't even have to talk to anybody.
- Just swipe.

19:24.540 --> 19:25.791
Just swipe it.

19:27.916 --> 19:30.750
- Bye, Dad.
- Oh, okay.

19:30.833 --> 19:32.833
- Say hi to Jerry for me.
- I will.

19:39.750 --> 19:41.875
Holy cow.
This is all yours?

19:42.458 --> 19:44.416
This is like
a college kid's dream room.

19:46.000 --> 19:47.166
Are you kidding?

19:47.250 --> 19:49.375
No college kid could afford this.

19:52.125 --> 19:53.916
The pool table alone
is 6 grand.

19:54.000 --> 19:55.334
And you use all this stuff?

19:55.416 --> 19:56.958
Of course, I do.

19:58.000 --> 19:59.458
What do you want to do first?

19:59.540 --> 20:00.665
Eight ball?

20:00.833 --> 20:02.708
Pump some iron?
I got <i>Madden.</i>

20:03.665 --> 20:04.916
And what the heck is that?

20:05.000 --> 20:06.500
That is a Onewheel.

20:06.875 --> 20:08.084
And they are fun.

20:08.458 --> 20:10.125
And you actually
ride that thing?

20:10.209 --> 20:11.209
Hells yes!

20:14.875 --> 20:15.916
Epic!

20:18.000 --> 20:19.500
Whoa!

20:24.000 --> 20:25.125
You should see me.

20:26.708 --> 20:28.791
- Wow!
- Yo, Jerry!

20:28.875 --> 20:31.291
Oh, sorry.
I didn't know you were <i>ocupado.</i>

20:31.540 --> 20:34.000
- This is my old friend Ed.
- Ed.

20:34.084 --> 20:35.334
- Danny.
- Hey. Danny.

20:35.415 --> 20:36.415
- Hi, Danny.
- Glad to meet you.

20:37.041 --> 20:38.375
So, uh, we walking?

20:38.458 --> 20:39.500
- Yeah.
- Oh, good.

20:39.583 --> 20:41.291
'Cause my masseuse told me

20:41.375 --> 20:43.250
if I got 10,000 steps
in this week,

20:43.334 --> 20:45.166
she would meet me
for coffee.

20:45.625 --> 20:48.125
- Ooh.
- And by coffee, I mean, you know...

20:48.458 --> 20:51.540
- Coffee?
- Yeah, coffee.

20:54.665 --> 20:56.500
- Morning, ladies.
- Really, dude?

20:57.791 --> 20:59.583
Those yoga pants
are gonna be the death of me.

20:59.665 --> 21:00.833
Why do you do that?

21:00.916 --> 21:02.958
What? They think I'm cute.

21:03.041 --> 21:05.041
Yeah, cute, like,
"Aren't old guys cute

21:05.125 --> 21:07.125
"when they still think
they have a shot?"

21:07.209 --> 21:09.875
Hey, I'm a catch.
You know, I got a full pension.

21:10.583 --> 21:13.125
Two more years,
I can ski free as a senior.

21:13.458 --> 21:15.583
- You ski?
- No, I do not.

21:16.084 --> 21:19.334
Morning.
Beautiful morning. How you doing?

21:19.415 --> 21:22.415
Nice, nice.
Next time bring up the pension.

21:22.500 --> 21:24.333
- Or the free skiing you'll never do.
- Oh.

21:24.415 --> 21:25.916
How's your daughter's place, Ed?

21:26.000 --> 21:27.084
It's okay, I guess.

21:28.084 --> 21:29.291
She gave me
my grandson's room.

21:29.375 --> 21:31.415
He's not too happy about it.

21:31.500 --> 21:32.916
He sent me this last night.

21:39.708 --> 21:40.708
Whoa!

21:41.583 --> 21:43.084
How did you respond?

21:43.708 --> 21:46.084
- I didn't.
- You're just gonna roll over on this?

21:46.166 --> 21:47.625
- You got to respond.
- Come on.

21:47.708 --> 21:50.583
This kind of aggression
shall not stand. <i>Semper Fi.</i>

21:50.666 --> 21:52.250
I didn't know
you were a Marine.

21:52.333 --> 21:54.125
I wasn't.
I'm just saying.

21:54.540 --> 21:57.166
Ah, he's a kid.
He's getting used to it, just like I am.

21:57.250 --> 21:58.375
I'm his grandfather.
So you know...

21:58.458 --> 21:59.875
He's not gonna do anything.

21:59.958 --> 22:02.125
What are you talking about?
You can't...

22:15.540 --> 22:17.875
Cotton candy, sweetie
<i>Go, let me see that Tootsie Roll</i>

22:17.959 --> 22:19.875
- <i>Come on, come on</i>
- <i>Tootsie Roll</i>

22:19.959 --> 22:21.875
<i>Just make that Tootsie Roll</i>

22:21.959 --> 22:23.458
- <i>Yeah, come on</i>
- <i>Tootsie Roll</i>

22:23.540 --> 22:25.333
<i>And make your Tootsie Roll</i>

22:25.415 --> 22:27.750
- <i>Here we go, here we go</i>
- <i>Tootsie Roll</i>

22:27.833 --> 22:29.333
<i>Just make that Tootsie Roll</i>

22:29.415 --> 22:30.959
<i>I want to see your Tootsie Roll</i>

22:31.041 --> 22:32.333
<i>Just make your Tootsie Roll</i>

22:32.415 --> 22:33.791
<i>To the left, to the left</i>

22:33.875 --> 22:35.583
<i>To the right, to the right</i>

22:35.666 --> 22:37.625
<i>To the front, to the front</i>

22:37.708 --> 22:39.250
<i>To the back, to the back...</i>

22:46.583 --> 22:49.000
"People who steal
other people's rooms

22:49.084 --> 22:50.290
"should not sleep well."

23:02.209 --> 23:03.791
Peter?

23:03.875 --> 23:04.875
Oh, Peter.

23:05.875 --> 23:08.333
Grandpa.
Is that you?

23:08.415 --> 23:10.415
Yeah, it's me.
You know it's me.

23:10.500 --> 23:11.875
You know what time it is?

23:13.458 --> 23:14.458
Nighttime?

23:14.540 --> 23:17.583
It's the middle of the night.
Come on. It's not funny, Peter.

23:17.666 --> 23:19.250
I don't like people
playing tricks on me,

23:19.333 --> 23:21.166
especially not
my own grandson.

23:21.250 --> 23:25.166
It's not a trick.
It's war.

23:26.708 --> 23:28.750
You don't go to war
against your family.

23:28.833 --> 23:30.959
You have to have an enemy to go to war,
and I'm not your enemy.

23:31.041 --> 23:34.791
You got my declaration.
Why didn't you say anything?

23:34.875 --> 23:36.708
Because I was
kind of hoping it was a joke.

23:36.791 --> 23:38.290
It's not a joke.

23:38.375 --> 23:40.625
You took something of mine,
and I want it back.

23:40.875 --> 23:42.916
Okay.
Go back to sleep.

23:43.000 --> 23:45.458
You made your point,
but this is over now.

23:48.541 --> 23:51.000
We'll see you in the morning,
which is almost here.

23:54.541 --> 23:57.375
Grandpa?
I love you.

23:58.625 --> 23:59.750
I love you, too, kiddo.

24:04.208 --> 24:05.333
But the war's still on.

24:17.500 --> 24:19.666
- Hi, Grandpa.
- Hey, Jenny.

24:19.750 --> 24:20.959
- Can I come in?
- Sure.

24:21.208 --> 24:22.208
Why not?

24:22.375 --> 24:23.916
'Cause when
Peter lived here,

24:24.458 --> 24:26.583
I wasn't allowed,
unless I sneaked.

24:26.666 --> 24:27.916
Come on, come on.

24:31.208 --> 24:33.290
- So, what can I do for you?
- Nothing.

24:33.375 --> 24:35.625
I just like to look
at other people's stuff.

24:37.000 --> 24:38.750
You know
it's my birthday coming up.

24:38.834 --> 24:39.834
That I do.

24:40.000 --> 24:41.791
Okay.
Just making sure.

24:45.541 --> 24:47.084
What's this?

24:47.165 --> 24:49.000
Those are marbles.

24:49.084 --> 24:50.084
Can I have one?

24:50.959 --> 24:52.791
Sure, if you promise
to take care of it,

24:52.875 --> 24:54.041
because they're
very special.

24:54.750 --> 24:56.708
They're not magic.

24:56.791 --> 25:00.290
People always think
their things are magic and they never are.

25:00.375 --> 25:02.791
No. I didn't say
that they were magic,

25:02.875 --> 25:04.875
but they are special.

25:05.125 --> 25:06.125
Come here.

25:08.834 --> 25:10.834
You remember how Grandpa
used to build houses?

25:10.916 --> 25:12.666
Yeah,
but I wasn't born.

25:12.750 --> 25:14.165
That's true,
you weren't born.

25:14.250 --> 25:16.041
But when you build a house,

25:16.125 --> 25:18.500
you always start
by doing some digging.

25:18.583 --> 25:21.000
And for some reason,
you almost always find marbles.

25:21.208 --> 25:23.750
I guess because they roll around
and get lost easily.

25:24.000 --> 25:26.666
But pretty much
every foundation I ever dug,

25:26.750 --> 25:28.458
I always found
a marble or two.

25:28.541 --> 25:29.834
So, guess what
I did with them?

25:29.916 --> 25:31.208
- What?
- I kept them.

25:31.541 --> 25:33.250
So, if you count
all those marbles,

25:33.333 --> 25:35.083
you'll know
how many houses I built.

25:35.290 --> 25:37.375
That's a lot of houses.

25:37.458 --> 25:39.500
I worked a long time.

25:39.583 --> 25:40.834
How come
you don't work now?

25:40.916 --> 25:42.959
Because I'm what
you call "retired."

25:43.333 --> 25:44.959
What's "retired"?

25:45.041 --> 25:48.165
It's when you stop working
so you can do other things.

25:48.834 --> 25:51.083
Like your grandmother and I
had big plans,

25:51.165 --> 25:54.625
but sometimes things
just don't work out.

25:56.125 --> 25:57.458
Can I have a marble now?

25:57.541 --> 25:58.541
Sure.

26:04.834 --> 26:05.834
What the...

26:09.250 --> 26:10.708
Careful, sweetheart.
Careful, careful.

26:23.791 --> 26:25.040
Are you okay, Grandpa?

26:25.125 --> 26:27.000
Yeah, yeah.
I'm just gonna rest

26:27.083 --> 26:29.165
down here for a while.

26:30.959 --> 26:32.583
Can I still have a marble?

26:32.666 --> 26:33.875
Take whatever you want.

26:39.000 --> 26:40.666
Oh, no.

26:40.750 --> 26:42.750
No, no.

26:42.834 --> 26:44.709
No.

26:46.416 --> 26:49.500
What's that racket upstairs?

26:49.583 --> 26:51.583
Grandpa lost his marbles.

27:18.208 --> 27:19.333
You wanted to see me?

27:19.416 --> 27:20.959
Yeah, come on in.

27:21.040 --> 27:22.250
Shut the door.

27:26.165 --> 27:27.208
Have a seat.

27:29.541 --> 27:30.875
So...

27:30.959 --> 27:33.625
You know that big jar
of marbles I had?

27:33.709 --> 27:36.040
No. How would I know
about the things you have

27:36.125 --> 27:37.625
in your room...

27:37.709 --> 27:39.165
that used to be mine?

27:39.250 --> 27:40.291
That's good.

27:40.375 --> 27:41.416
That's funny.

27:41.666 --> 27:42.834
That's real funny.

27:42.916 --> 27:44.834
Everybody likes a funny kid.

27:46.000 --> 27:47.416
I thought we were done with this.

27:47.500 --> 27:49.250
All you have to do
is tell Mom and Dad

27:49.333 --> 27:50.791
that you want
to switch rooms with me.

27:50.875 --> 27:52.125
And then it'll be done.

27:52.208 --> 27:54.291
You really want a war?

27:54.375 --> 27:56.040
Because, you know,
I've been in one.

27:56.125 --> 27:57.583
And it's not like video games.

27:57.666 --> 27:59.416
Even if you win,
everybody gets hurt.

27:59.500 --> 28:01.000
I only want what's mine.

28:01.083 --> 28:02.375
By playing hardball, huh?

28:02.583 --> 28:03.875
I'm not playing.

28:03.958 --> 28:05.291
Fair enough.

28:06.834 --> 28:09.083
So, what are the rules of engagement?

28:09.165 --> 28:10.458
The what?

28:10.541 --> 28:12.875
Rules of engagement.

28:12.958 --> 28:15.291
What's allowed
and not allowed.

28:15.375 --> 28:16.875
You don't have rules
in a war.

28:16.958 --> 28:18.416
Oh, yes, you do.

28:20.083 --> 28:21.165
"Rule number one...

28:21.791 --> 28:24.040
"No collateral damage

28:24.125 --> 28:27.333
"to civilians
or their property."

28:27.416 --> 28:30.625
That means it can't affect
your parents or your sisters.

28:30.915 --> 28:32.416
Agreed.

28:32.500 --> 28:34.541
"Rule number two...

28:34.625 --> 28:35.834
"No telling."

28:35.915 --> 28:37.375
This is man-to-man,

28:37.458 --> 28:39.000
just between me and you.

28:39.750 --> 28:41.584
No ratting the other guy out.

28:41.666 --> 28:42.791
Agreed.

28:43.291 --> 28:45.125
Okay. Sign.

28:57.375 --> 28:59.040
Okay.

28:59.125 --> 29:01.458
You got your wish, Secret Warrior.

29:01.541 --> 29:03.000
Okay...

29:03.083 --> 29:04.584
Senior Soldier.

29:09.165 --> 29:10.416
But from now on,

29:10.500 --> 29:11.709
you better watch out.

29:17.165 --> 29:18.915
<i>The jungle...</i>

29:19.000 --> 29:21.458
<i>a place where animals
both big and small,</i>

29:22.125 --> 29:24.208
<i>exotic and bizarre,</i>

29:24.291 --> 29:27.625
<i>coexist with one another
in the same space</i>

29:27.709 --> 29:30.584
<i>and in the same time.</i>

29:30.666 --> 29:33.791
<i>The game... to survive.</i>

29:33.875 --> 29:36.791
<i>The stakes... life and death.</i>

29:37.750 --> 29:41.625
<i>Those who strike first
live to see another day.</i>

29:42.584 --> 29:44.125
<i>Those who sleep</i>

29:44.208 --> 29:45.875
<i>will be eaten alive.</i>

29:54.208 --> 29:58.709
<i>I've heard people whisper</i>

29:58.791 --> 30:03.750
<i>That you aren't being true</i>

30:03.833 --> 30:07.208
<i>I just let them whisper</i>

30:07.291 --> 30:13.375
<i>'Cause all I've got is you</i>

30:13.458 --> 30:16.791
<i>I've gotta believe</i>

30:16.875 --> 30:19.833
<i>In something</i>

30:19.915 --> 30:21.000
<i>I've gotta believe...</i>

30:35.625 --> 30:38.666
Okay. Okay.

30:59.416 --> 31:00.416
What the...

31:03.125 --> 31:04.875
What is this stuff?

31:07.750 --> 31:09.750
Fast-drying foam sealant.

31:10.416 --> 31:12.083
I'm gonna kill this kid.

31:13.208 --> 31:14.584
You don't mess with me,
you little...

31:18.000 --> 31:19.166
You think you're cute?

31:19.250 --> 31:21.666
You've welcomed a world of pain,
my friend.

31:21.958 --> 31:24.416
You'll be sorry.
Mess with me, you little...

31:27.915 --> 31:29.958
Think you're cute?
You're not cute!

31:30.958 --> 31:32.040
Ah!

31:33.915 --> 31:35.790
Oh!

31:37.915 --> 31:39.709
Oh!

31:39.875 --> 31:41.208
Oh!

31:41.459 --> 31:43.375
This will never be spoken of.

31:43.459 --> 31:45.500
No idea what you're talking about.

31:49.416 --> 31:50.584
Oh!

31:51.041 --> 31:53.459
You're doing very well,
Grandpa.

31:53.541 --> 31:54.541
Thank you, sweetheart.

31:54.625 --> 31:56.166
You're a very good teacher.

31:57.166 --> 31:58.915
Why is your face all red?

31:59.000 --> 32:00.416
I don't know.

32:01.166 --> 32:03.833
I may be allergic
to something in this house.

32:04.958 --> 32:06.915
I'm off to shaving cream.

32:07.000 --> 32:08.790
I mean, school.

32:08.875 --> 32:11.750
Uh, Peter, is that your binder?

32:13.500 --> 32:14.915
Yeah. Thanks.

32:17.750 --> 32:19.584
Have a good day at school,
kiddo.

32:19.666 --> 32:20.875
Love you.

32:28.166 --> 32:29.208
Hey, Pete.

32:29.291 --> 32:31.334
How's your super unnecessary
war going?

32:31.416 --> 32:34.041
Not good.
I was up all night.

32:34.125 --> 32:35.250
Couldn't sleep at all.

32:35.541 --> 32:38.083
- Diarrhea?
- What? No.

32:38.875 --> 32:40.000
My grandpa.

32:40.083 --> 32:41.291
Your grandpa had diarrhea?

32:41.375 --> 32:43.958
No. There's no diarrhea
in this story.

32:44.541 --> 32:45.625
Oh.

32:46.125 --> 32:48.083
I did what
you said yesterday,

32:48.166 --> 32:50.000
and I hit him good
multiple times.

32:50.083 --> 32:52.208
I even put hot sauce
in his coffee this morning.

32:52.833 --> 32:54.125
<i>So far, nothing.</i>

33:07.375 --> 33:09.625
Dude, your grandfather's using psyops.

33:09.708 --> 33:11.584
Psychological warfare.

33:11.665 --> 33:14.334
Or maybe he's just
being an adult.

33:14.416 --> 33:17.790
Peter, if you're done talking,
maybe you'd like to read us

33:17.875 --> 33:20.125
your report on what you did
over your summer vacation?

33:20.208 --> 33:21.541
Yeah. Sure.

33:24.541 --> 33:26.790
"My Summer Vacation"
by Peter Decker.

33:26.875 --> 33:29.459
"This summer was one
of the best summer breaks I've ever had.

33:29.541 --> 33:31.584
"I rode my bike a lot
and stopped showering

33:31.665 --> 33:33.915
"until I smelled
like a monkey's butt."

33:37.000 --> 33:39.125
Keep reading, Peter.
Go on.

33:39.208 --> 33:41.125
- I don't want to. This isn't my...
- Read.

33:44.000 --> 33:46.625
"During my vacation,

33:46.708 --> 33:49.833
"I figured out how to freeze
my own farts in a baggie."

33:52.833 --> 33:54.208
I didn't write this!

33:54.291 --> 33:55.416
Have a seat.

33:55.583 --> 33:57.416
And see me after class.

34:02.790 --> 34:03.832
Psyops.

34:21.458 --> 34:22.498
Amateur.

34:42.373 --> 34:44.000
What's going on here?

34:44.081 --> 34:46.625
Nothing. Nothing. We were just, um...

34:46.708 --> 34:49.416
I was just dropping off
some vocabulary drills.

34:49.500 --> 34:51.458
- Really?
- Vocabulary.

34:52.083 --> 34:53.750
Russell, go.

34:55.250 --> 34:56.416
Mia, stay.

34:57.875 --> 34:59.000
Do we not have a policy

34:59.083 --> 35:01.541
about no boys in this house
when no one is here?

35:01.625 --> 35:03.791
Oh, my God, Mom,
don't blow a gasket.

35:03.875 --> 35:05.041
We weren't doing anything.

35:05.125 --> 35:06.708
Don't you think
I was your age once?

35:06.791 --> 35:08.583
- No, I don't.
- Really?

35:08.666 --> 35:10.833
- Yeah, 'cause you are...
- What?

35:10.916 --> 35:13.083
- You are literally... You are...
- Say it.

35:15.125 --> 35:17.875
Those vocabulary drills
are paying off, sweetie.

35:17.958 --> 35:18.958
Ugh!

35:41.750 --> 35:42.875
What the heck?

35:43.791 --> 35:45.166
Whoa!

35:52.375 --> 35:54.708
Don't start nothing,
won't be nothing.

35:56.375 --> 35:57.500
He got me.

36:01.625 --> 36:04.083
I got him good.
Tape on the doorway.

36:04.166 --> 36:06.208
Like I wouldn't
see that coming from a mile away.

36:06.291 --> 36:08.208
- Rookie!
- Tape on the doorway.

36:08.291 --> 36:09.750
Tape on the doorway.

36:10.166 --> 36:11.458
Step back, boys.
Big hitter.

36:11.541 --> 36:13.125
- All right.
- Yep. Stepping back.

36:23.666 --> 36:24.833
We should skip this hole.

36:24.916 --> 36:26.416
- Yeah, good idea. Come on.
- Yeah.

36:31.125 --> 36:33.666
I wonder how my grandpa's
golf game is... going.

36:34.500 --> 36:35.541
My Jordans.

36:38.916 --> 36:42.750
Dude, I think
your grandpa might be a ninja.

36:43.250 --> 36:44.750
My Jordans!

37:03.875 --> 37:04.916
First time?

37:05.000 --> 37:06.750
Unfortunately, no.

37:07.958 --> 37:09.458
What are you,
a spy or something?

37:09.541 --> 37:12.041
No, I'm just trying
to outsmart my grandson.

37:12.125 --> 37:14.541
We're in the middle of
a turf battle over a bedroom.

37:14.625 --> 37:16.666
I just moved into
my daughter's house, so...

37:16.750 --> 37:18.291
No, no, no,
don't say anything else.

37:18.375 --> 37:20.083
That way,
they can't make me testify.

37:20.916 --> 37:22.166
I won't.

37:23.750 --> 37:24.750
You need a hand?

37:24.833 --> 37:26.458
No, let me give it
one more shot.

37:28.541 --> 37:31.416
Oh, come on.
Yeah, I...

37:31.500 --> 37:32.708
All right,
what am I doing wrong now?

37:32.791 --> 37:35.083
Oh! No, I'm not
gonna help you now.

37:35.166 --> 37:37.750
- That way, you'll never learn.
- Making it tough on me, huh?

37:41.375 --> 37:42.791
You're on your way.

37:45.958 --> 37:46.958
<i>Bam!</i>

37:47.041 --> 37:49.833
<i>Cars like this
1974 Volkswagen Bug use...</i>

37:49.916 --> 37:51.208
We had one of those, remember?

37:51.291 --> 37:53.291
- We changed the clutch on it.
- Yeah, how could I forget?

37:53.375 --> 37:54.666
You dropped the flywheel
on my toe.

37:54.750 --> 37:58.625
That was your fault
for mistaking me for your son.

37:58.708 --> 38:00.416
Anybody want to watch
anything else, maybe?

38:00.500 --> 38:02.166
Like, uh, Netflix?

38:03.083 --> 38:04.208
Weather Channel?

38:04.708 --> 38:06.541
C-SPAN?

38:06.625 --> 38:08.041
<i>The Grinch
Who Stole Christmas.</i>

38:08.125 --> 38:09.166
Hey, yeah.

38:09.333 --> 38:10.875
Hey. Going to Skyler's house.

38:11.125 --> 38:12.833
What? Now?

38:13.375 --> 38:14.625
Yeah. I'm studying.

38:15.541 --> 38:17.958
Do you want me to get
into a good college or not?

38:20.541 --> 38:21.666
Okay. Bye.

38:22.916 --> 38:24.833
She's going to see Russell.
I know it.

38:26.958 --> 38:29.375
- What?
- None of my business.

38:29.458 --> 38:31.000
No, come on.
You're gonna say it anyway.

38:31.083 --> 38:32.500
Okay.

38:32.583 --> 38:35.291
My advice about fighting
with her about her boyfriend is don't.

38:35.500 --> 38:37.375
It cost me
two years with you.

38:37.833 --> 38:38.833
Yeah.

38:38.916 --> 38:40.166
When you started
dating Artie here.

38:40.250 --> 38:41.875
That's not true.
I don't remember that.

38:41.958 --> 38:43.333
I do.
It was terrible.

38:43.416 --> 38:45.166
I was over at the house
all the time.

38:45.250 --> 38:46.916
Yeah, you were
over at the house talking to your mother.

38:47.000 --> 38:48.500
You barely talked
to me at all.

38:49.708 --> 38:50.916
Oh.

38:51.000 --> 38:52.125
- Really?
- Yeah.

38:52.791 --> 38:54.083
Um... Sorry, Dad.

38:54.166 --> 38:55.541
No, don't be.
It was my fault.

38:55.625 --> 38:56.875
I thought he wasn't
good enough for you,

38:56.958 --> 38:59.125
till I realized
that wasn't the point.

38:59.625 --> 39:01.541
The point was you thought
he was good enough for you.

39:02.291 --> 39:04.750
But you and Arthur
get along great now.

39:04.833 --> 39:06.416
Because I stopped
being an idiot.

39:06.500 --> 39:08.625
But I'll never get
those two years back.

39:09.833 --> 39:11.166
Wow. Uh...

39:11.541 --> 39:12.916
I appreciate that, Ed.

39:13.000 --> 39:16.666
You're welcome, Artie. I mean,
I meant that, sincerely.

39:16.750 --> 39:18.750
But the career,
not so much.

39:19.083 --> 39:20.250
What?

39:20.666 --> 39:21.833
Dad!

39:21.916 --> 39:23.583
Nothing against Artie.
It's just that I think

39:23.666 --> 39:25.833
that people who lose sight
of their dreams

39:25.916 --> 39:27.916
and settle for less
are never very happy.

39:28.000 --> 39:29.000
That's all.

39:29.083 --> 39:31.791
Really?
I find that those same people

39:31.875 --> 39:33.958
tend to have
secure incomes.

39:34.041 --> 39:37.000
Which then allow them to,
I don't know,

39:37.083 --> 39:39.083
take in an aging senior,
perhaps.

39:39.166 --> 39:40.708
And the name's Arthur.

39:41.958 --> 39:44.500
Come on, honey.
Let's go. It's bedtime.

39:44.583 --> 39:45.583
Here we go.

39:45.666 --> 39:47.166
Night, sweetie.

39:47.250 --> 39:48.500
- Night.
- Good night.

39:50.333 --> 39:52.666
I thought you stopped
being an idiot.

39:54.000 --> 39:55.083
Sorry.

40:04.625 --> 40:06.375
I can't put anything
back together.

40:06.458 --> 40:08.083
He took all of the screws.

40:08.166 --> 40:10.000
So now I'm sleeping
on the floor.

40:10.083 --> 40:11.250
<i>That's hilarious.</i>

40:11.666 --> 40:12.916
Yeah. Ha ha.

40:13.000 --> 40:14.458
<i>Dude, you might have
to face the fact</i>

40:14.541 --> 40:16.041
<i>that your grandfather's
just smarter than you.</i>

40:16.125 --> 40:18.458
- Hey!
- <i>Billy, nice snake.</i>

40:18.541 --> 40:19.541
<i>Thanks.</i>

40:19.625 --> 40:22.708
<i>Steven, I found the dog
chewing your snuggables again.</i>

40:22.916 --> 40:25.166
<i>Those aren't mine.</i>

40:25.541 --> 40:26.583
<i>Really?</i>

40:26.666 --> 40:29.250
<i>It says "Captain Steve"
on the waistband.</i>

40:29.333 --> 40:32.541
- <i>Get out of my room!</i>
- <i>Captain Steve.</i>

40:42.083 --> 40:44.166
- See? Not that hard.
- Yeah.

40:44.250 --> 40:45.541
Thanks, kiddo.

40:45.625 --> 40:47.458
Okay, off you go.

40:47.541 --> 40:48.791
Skedaddle. Thanks.

40:55.083 --> 40:57.250
Yeah. Now you're talking.

40:59.375 --> 41:01.000
<i>I know something
you could do, Peter.</i>

41:01.083 --> 41:02.375
- What?
- <i>You could use</i>

41:02.458 --> 41:04.083
<i>some of the mental energy
you're expending</i>

41:04.166 --> 41:05.666
<i>on thinking up
stupid tricks</i>

41:05.750 --> 41:08.750
<i>to play on your grandfather
to not get a C in math.</i>

41:08.833 --> 41:12.000
Who cares about math?
This is real life.

41:12.083 --> 41:15.166
<i>Said the guy building
a fake castle in a video game.</i>

41:15.250 --> 41:17.666
Petersburg isn't a castle.

41:17.750 --> 41:18.916
<i>It's a palace.</i>

41:19.000 --> 41:22.250
And after three years in the making,
it's almost finished.

41:22.541 --> 41:24.333
Too easy.

41:32.125 --> 41:33.125
No.

41:33.208 --> 41:34.625
Uh-oh.

41:35.875 --> 41:38.250
And then see
if the light comes back on.

41:39.250 --> 41:40.750
No!

41:41.291 --> 41:43.458
Any nimrod knows that.

41:49.083 --> 41:50.208
What the...

42:20.375 --> 42:21.416
Did you bring it?

42:21.500 --> 42:22.666
You got the cash?

42:27.625 --> 42:28.875
Dude, it's all there.

42:28.958 --> 42:31.458
I'm sure it is, Pete.
I'm sure it is.

42:54.500 --> 42:56.041
Not funny, Peter.

42:56.916 --> 42:58.041
Nice snake.

42:58.125 --> 42:59.458
Nice, nice snake.
Nice snake.

42:59.541 --> 43:01.333
Nice. Take all the room
you want.

43:01.416 --> 43:02.416
Do whatever you want.

43:02.958 --> 43:04.958
I'm just gonna go...

43:05.041 --> 43:06.291
Go over here.

43:14.000 --> 43:15.958
Don't mind if I do, Eddie.

43:22.708 --> 43:24.125
You stay there.
You stay there.

43:24.500 --> 43:25.833
You stay there.

44:10.791 --> 44:11.791
What's that?

44:11.875 --> 44:13.791
It's a Vitalert necklace.

44:13.875 --> 44:15.125
A what?

44:15.208 --> 44:16.958
Like those TV commercials?

44:17.041 --> 44:18.833
You expect me to wear that?

44:18.916 --> 44:20.583
Absolutely not.

44:20.666 --> 44:22.666
Absolutely not.
No way.

44:22.750 --> 44:24.541
- Look. You know, you just...
- No.

44:24.625 --> 44:25.791
You wear it
under your shirt,

44:25.875 --> 44:27.833
and, hey, nobody can
even see it.

44:27.916 --> 44:29.041
- You can't see that.
- Right?

44:29.125 --> 44:30.375
If you don't want
to wear it for you,

44:30.458 --> 44:31.875
wear it for me.

44:32.458 --> 44:34.000
But I don't need this.

44:34.083 --> 44:35.541
- Really?
- I don't need this.

44:35.625 --> 44:38.875
Because Arthur says
that you've been acting...

44:39.791 --> 44:41.166
Oddly.

44:41.250 --> 44:43.541
- He has?
- For the record,

44:43.625 --> 44:45.583
I didn't say "oddly."

44:45.666 --> 44:47.333
I said "confused."

44:48.666 --> 44:50.291
- Confused?
- Look, Dad,

44:50.375 --> 44:53.000
is it so hard to believe
that we care about you?

44:53.083 --> 44:54.416
Probably won't even need
to use it.

44:54.500 --> 44:56.833
You got that right,
'cause I'm not wearing it.

44:56.916 --> 44:59.625
Look, it gives me
peace of mind to know

44:59.708 --> 45:01.625
that with just one push
of a button,

45:01.708 --> 45:03.541
you can get help
if you need it.

45:08.000 --> 45:09.166
Please?

45:09.916 --> 45:11.083
Please.

45:25.083 --> 45:26.791
Sweet necklace, Grandpa.

45:26.875 --> 45:29.166
For every action, my friend.

45:44.541 --> 45:45.958
Ugh!

46:20.083 --> 46:21.500
Ugh!

46:24.625 --> 46:26.416
And this is how
you found him?

46:26.500 --> 46:28.166
Yeah.

46:28.250 --> 46:31.083
When I couldn't reach him online,
I got worried.

46:31.916 --> 46:36.000
My life's work...
Ruined!

46:36.083 --> 46:38.583
All I see is a pile of rubble.

46:38.666 --> 46:40.916
He destroyed Petersburg!

46:41.000 --> 46:43.583
I've been building it for more
than a third of my life.

46:43.666 --> 46:46.208
Actually, three over 12
is exactly 25%,

46:46.291 --> 46:48.375
which is less than a third
of your life.

46:50.333 --> 46:51.500
Well, it is.

46:52.916 --> 46:53.916
It's okay, buddy.

47:28.208 --> 47:30.416
Oh. You see, dear?

47:30.500 --> 47:32.708
I was right.
The boy's coming around.

47:32.791 --> 47:35.875
Do you both promise
to use your words?

47:35.958 --> 47:37.666
I promise.

47:37.750 --> 47:39.208
Why are we
doing it this way?

47:39.291 --> 47:41.416
Because,
when you have peace talks,

47:41.500 --> 47:43.416
you need someone neutral
to mediate.

47:43.500 --> 47:45.541
Otherwise,
it just breaks down into yelling.

47:45.625 --> 47:47.375
- This is dumb!
- Well, we're doing it.

47:47.458 --> 47:48.750
Besides, it took me
five minutes

47:48.833 --> 47:50.583
to get in this chair,
and I'm not getting out.

47:51.250 --> 47:54.166
Grandpa promised.
You have to promise.

47:54.625 --> 47:57.333
Okay, fine.
I promise.

47:57.416 --> 48:00.000
Good.
Now, I will admit

48:00.083 --> 48:01.500
that hostilities may have
escalated

48:01.583 --> 48:02.958
more than either of us
anticipated.

48:03.041 --> 48:05.416
You don't touch
another man's computer!

48:05.500 --> 48:06.666
That's not cool!

48:06.750 --> 48:08.500
That's what war
is all about, kiddo.

48:08.583 --> 48:11.208
War. I just want
my room back!

48:11.291 --> 48:14.333
- No yelling.
- I'm not yelling. He's yelling.

48:14.416 --> 48:16.208
Say you're sorry
to Grandpa.

48:16.291 --> 48:17.750
No, it's okay,
sweetheart.

48:17.833 --> 48:18.958
I love you, Grandpa.

48:19.041 --> 48:20.083
I love you, too.

48:21.000 --> 48:22.416
- Stop that!
- Stop what?

48:22.500 --> 48:24.458
- What's going on here?
- Nothing's going on here.

48:24.541 --> 48:25.541
You're supposed to
be neutral!

48:25.625 --> 48:27.541
I don't even know
what that means.

48:27.625 --> 48:30.833
It means you shouldn't
act like you like him better than me.

48:30.916 --> 48:32.750
I do like him
better than you.

48:32.833 --> 48:34.083
He gave me a cookie.

48:35.750 --> 48:37.333
Okay, that sounds worse
than it is.

48:37.416 --> 48:39.750
It is true a cookie was given,
but it was way before

48:39.833 --> 48:41.750
this negotiation
had even been scheduled.

48:42.958 --> 48:45.791
Chocolate chip,
my favorite.

48:46.250 --> 48:47.875
Mine, too.

48:47.958 --> 48:48.958
That's it.

48:49.041 --> 48:50.791
I'm done.
Peace is canceled.

48:50.875 --> 48:53.458
- No yelling.
- Shut up!

48:53.541 --> 48:55.750
- Shut up's a bad word.
- Peter.

48:56.416 --> 48:58.166
Can I have
my second cookie now?

48:58.250 --> 48:59.833
Peter, hold on.
Please.

48:59.916 --> 49:01.125
Come on.
You're right.

49:01.208 --> 49:02.500
A cookie may have
been involved,

49:02.583 --> 49:05.458
which may have been an attempt
to influence the mediator,

49:05.541 --> 49:09.041
which, in retrospect,
may have been inappropriate.

49:09.125 --> 49:11.000
- May have been?
- Okay, to be fair,

49:11.083 --> 49:13.541
you entered negotiations with
a bit of an attitude yourself.

49:13.625 --> 49:15.625
You didn't really give peace
a chance, either.

49:15.708 --> 49:19.125
Why should I?
You demolished Petersburg.

49:19.208 --> 49:21.666
But that's what I've been
trying to tell you when this all started.

49:21.750 --> 49:23.916
War is no game, Peter.

49:24.000 --> 49:26.541
Only kids and fools
and generals think that.

49:26.625 --> 49:27.625
War hurts.

49:27.708 --> 49:31.041
War wounds and kills
and causes misery.

49:31.125 --> 49:33.041
We got to end this somehow.

49:33.125 --> 49:34.916
How?

49:35.000 --> 49:38.250
What if we have one final competition,
winner take all?

49:38.333 --> 49:40.833
- What kind of competition?
- I don't know. You pick.

49:40.916 --> 49:43.083
Whatever you want, I'll do it
and this whole thing will be over.

49:43.625 --> 49:45.333
- Whatever I want?
- Whatever you want.

49:48.333 --> 49:49.583
Okay.

49:51.708 --> 49:52.750
It's not a date.

49:52.958 --> 49:54.666
It's just that
we need a fourth for the team

49:54.750 --> 49:57.458
and it needs to be a woman,
and I don't know anyone else.

49:58.250 --> 49:59.250
So, let me
get this straight.

49:59.333 --> 50:01.041
You want me
to help you and your buddies

50:01.125 --> 50:03.416
to beat up your grandson
and his buddies,

50:03.500 --> 50:04.875
because the two of you
can't figure out

50:04.958 --> 50:06.916
some way to live
in the same house?

50:07.583 --> 50:09.291
Well, when you put it
like that...

50:09.375 --> 50:10.500
I'm in.

50:11.166 --> 50:13.958
My granddaughter can be
a pain in the butt sometimes.

50:22.208 --> 50:23.208
Whoo!

50:26.416 --> 50:28.041
Holy Mary, we're dead.

50:28.291 --> 50:30.208
It's just an intimidation tactic, Danny.

50:30.416 --> 50:32.208
Don't let them see your fear.

50:32.416 --> 50:33.666
They feed off that.

50:33.750 --> 50:35.916
They're like baby velociraptors.

50:36.000 --> 50:38.166
Yeah. We're up.

50:39.875 --> 50:41.916
Do you guys even remember
how to play dodgeball?

50:42.000 --> 50:44.458
Did they
even have dodgeball in the 1800s?

50:44.541 --> 50:46.625
They had wiseass kids,
I know that.

50:46.708 --> 50:48.583
And just remember,
no headsies.

50:48.666 --> 50:49.708
And no nutsies.

50:49.875 --> 50:51.250
No aiming for the junk.

50:51.541 --> 50:52.666
Yeah. What he said.

50:52.750 --> 50:54.166
Hope you brought your Poligrip, old man,

50:54.250 --> 50:55.666
'cause those false teeth
are coming out.

50:55.750 --> 50:57.250
Big words for a little baby.

50:57.750 --> 50:59.750
Sure you don't need
your diaper changed?

51:00.208 --> 51:01.291
Sure you don't?

51:01.375 --> 51:03.166
Ooh!

51:03.250 --> 51:04.958
- Men.
- Tell me about it.

51:05.166 --> 51:07.041
You're gonna love the attic, Grandpa.

51:07.208 --> 51:08.875
We're gonna see about that,
Petey boy.

51:08.958 --> 51:10.583
Let's get it on.

51:10.666 --> 51:11.875
Let's get it on!

51:24.375 --> 51:25.375
Hi.

51:25.458 --> 51:26.791
Run for your lives!

51:27.250 --> 51:28.250
Fire!

51:30.208 --> 51:32.250
I'm already regretting
agreeing to do this.

51:34.500 --> 51:35.541
Man down.

51:38.041 --> 51:39.958
Hey! We said no headsies.

51:40.291 --> 51:42.291
Oops. It slipped.

51:42.375 --> 51:44.166
Punk.

