Unless you call
getting punched in the face

01:07:56.875 --> 01:07:58.666
by a giant eighth-grader exciting.

01:07:58.958 --> 01:07:59.958
Really?

01:08:00.208 --> 01:08:01.333
Yep.

01:08:01.416 --> 01:08:03.458
- What happened?
- He was blasted into a giant

01:08:03.541 --> 01:08:06.291
orangesicle...
as soon as he opened up my backpack.

01:08:07.541 --> 01:08:09.458
It's so weird, right?

01:08:09.623 --> 01:08:10.666
Hello, boys!

01:08:11.166 --> 01:08:12.875
- Hey, Dad.
- Hey...

01:08:12.958 --> 01:08:14.500
Let me set this stuff down,
and I'll help you

01:08:14.583 --> 01:08:15.833
put the lights on the roof
there, Ed.

01:08:15.916 --> 01:08:17.125
Thanks, Arthur.

01:08:18.663 --> 01:08:19.957
I said "Arthur."

01:08:20.875 --> 01:08:23.082
Don't you two make
a nice team.

01:08:23.791 --> 01:08:25.750
Jenny's birthday's gonna be
so exciting.

01:08:25.957 --> 01:08:28.207
All that's left to do
is try to find a Santa Claus

01:08:28.292 --> 01:08:30.167
in early September,
and we'll be golden.

01:08:30.417 --> 01:08:31.625
Don't you worry yourself.

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:33.372
I know Santa personally.

01:08:33.457 --> 01:08:34.750
Consider it done.

01:08:34.957 --> 01:08:36.250
Aw!

01:08:36.497 --> 01:08:37.957
Thanks, Dad.
That's so sweet.

01:08:38.042 --> 01:08:40.125
It's the least I can do for Jenny.

01:08:41.541 --> 01:08:45.000
Mom, before you say no,
hear me out.

01:08:45.666 --> 01:08:47.832
Can Russell come
to Jennifer's birthday party?

01:08:48.417 --> 01:08:50.000
- No.
- What?

01:08:50.582 --> 01:08:52.582
Why? Peter's friends get to go.

01:08:52.666 --> 01:08:54.207
That reminds me,
I invited Jerry

01:08:54.292 --> 01:08:55.457
and the crew,
if that's okay.

01:08:55.541 --> 01:08:57.042
No, that's great.

01:08:57.125 --> 01:08:58.875
And you don't see
how unfair this is?

01:09:00.582 --> 01:09:02.125
I hate you!

01:09:04.457 --> 01:09:06.125
I don't want to hear it.

01:09:06.750 --> 01:09:08.247
Hey, Peter.

01:09:08.332 --> 01:09:09.707
Yeah?

01:09:11.250 --> 01:09:13.207
Listen... You know,

01:09:13.292 --> 01:09:16.457
in World War I,
the Germans and the British

01:09:16.538 --> 01:09:18.292
put down their weapons
on Christmas Eve

01:09:18.375 --> 01:09:20.125
in favor of celebrating
rather than fighting

01:09:20.207 --> 01:09:21.497
- during the holiday.
- Hmm.

01:09:21.582 --> 01:09:24.332
Your sister's birthday
is a special occasion

01:09:24.500 --> 01:09:25.917
and should be celebrated.

01:09:26.292 --> 01:09:27.500
I guess you're right.

01:09:27.582 --> 01:09:29.082
Okay, then let's agree...

01:09:29.166 --> 01:09:31.500
Temporary armistice for Jenny.

01:09:32.666 --> 01:09:33.792
Deal?

01:09:35.207 --> 01:09:36.750
Deal.

01:09:45.082 --> 01:09:46.792
Please! Stop it.

01:09:50.957 --> 01:09:52.457
Ow! Cut it out!

01:09:52.541 --> 01:09:54.541
- You're hurting me.
- "You're hurting me."

01:09:55.625 --> 01:09:57.125
That looks like fun.

01:09:57.208 --> 01:09:58.957
Yeah, lots of fun.

01:09:59.500 --> 01:10:01.250
We like fun, too.

01:10:03.582 --> 01:10:05.707
Forgot I had detention today.

01:10:06.625 --> 01:10:08.125
Looks like you're on your own.

01:10:08.582 --> 01:10:09.582
I have a question.

01:10:09.666 --> 01:10:11.625
Do you know my grandson
Peter Decker?

01:10:13.457 --> 01:10:14.832
Thought so.

01:10:19.000 --> 01:10:20.125
- Dumpster.
- What? Wait, wait.

01:10:20.208 --> 01:10:22.707
Don't make this harder
than it has to be, kid.

01:10:22.792 --> 01:10:25.375
Come on,
take your lumps like a man.

01:10:25.457 --> 01:10:27.208
- Who are you guys?
- Come on.

01:10:27.375 --> 01:10:29.042
Disciplinary board.

01:10:31.500 --> 01:10:33.125
Leave Peter alone,
understood?

01:10:33.208 --> 01:10:34.792
Whoa! Ripe.

01:10:34.875 --> 01:10:36.917
Not your lucky day,
tough guy.

01:10:37.125 --> 01:10:38.250
- Get him in there.
- No!

01:10:38.333 --> 01:10:39.375
No! Don't...

01:10:39.457 --> 01:10:40.750
No!

01:10:41.625 --> 01:10:43.582
Nasty!

01:10:43.792 --> 01:10:45.208
Get me out of here!

01:10:46.792 --> 01:10:48.125
Hello?

01:10:50.457 --> 01:10:51.457
Wow!

01:10:53.541 --> 01:10:56.167
Merry birthday, sweetheart.

01:10:56.666 --> 01:10:58.625
<i>Hey</i>

01:11:01.375 --> 01:11:03.457
<i>Ooh, hoo</i>

01:11:04.208 --> 01:11:06.917
<i>Hurry home and come round here</i>

01:11:07.000 --> 01:11:10.208
<i>I really love
this time of year</i>

01:11:10.292 --> 01:11:12.832
<i>Making plans
to get together</i>

01:11:12.917 --> 01:11:16.208
<i>Memories that will
last forever</i>

01:11:16.292 --> 01:11:18.957
<i>Sharing laughter and
sharing joy</i>

01:11:19.042 --> 01:11:21.875
<i>Everyone is singing,
all the girls and boys</i>

01:11:22.042 --> 01:11:24.875
<i>Some kind of magic
is in the air</i>

01:11:24.957 --> 01:11:28.416
<i>To make a special moment
we can share</i>

01:11:28.500 --> 01:11:30.457
<i>The snow is falling...</i>

01:11:30.832 --> 01:11:32.500
It's quiet.

01:11:32.582 --> 01:11:33.832
Too quiet.

01:11:33.917 --> 01:11:35.125
Billy, they agreed.

01:11:35.208 --> 01:11:36.792
His grandpa's not gonna do anything.

01:11:37.042 --> 01:11:38.917
If my grandpa makes a move,
I'll be ready.

01:11:39.917 --> 01:11:41.208
See that Santa chair?

01:11:41.292 --> 01:11:42.375
Yeah.

01:11:42.582 --> 01:11:43.875
I booby-trapped it.

01:11:44.332 --> 01:11:46.292
Did somebody say "boobies"?

01:11:46.375 --> 01:11:48.000
Go away, Steve.

01:11:49.750 --> 01:11:51.416
This eggnog tastes funny.

01:11:52.416 --> 01:11:53.792
Let me fix it for you.

01:11:54.375 --> 01:11:55.375
Ooh!

01:12:00.208 --> 01:12:01.875
Hey, everybody!

01:12:02.208 --> 01:12:03.832
Guess who's here!

01:12:03.917 --> 01:12:06.083
Ho, ho, ho!
Merry Christmas.

01:12:06.167 --> 01:12:07.582
Here comes Santa.

01:12:09.250 --> 01:12:10.792
Santa!

01:12:10.875 --> 01:12:12.792
Better watch out,
better not pout.

01:12:12.875 --> 01:12:14.958
I got toys and goodies.
I got everything.

01:12:15.042 --> 01:12:16.375
Wait a sec.

01:12:16.457 --> 01:12:18.083
That's not my grandpa.

01:12:18.792 --> 01:12:19.917
Ed?

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:22.083
No, thanks.
Got to stay alert.

01:12:22.375 --> 01:12:23.875
Just in case.

01:12:23.958 --> 01:12:26.582
Kid wouldn't have the <i>cojones</i>
to do anything. You shook on it.

01:12:26.667 --> 01:12:28.457
You never know.
You can't trust these kids.

01:12:29.042 --> 01:12:30.167
Hey, Grandpa.

01:12:30.250 --> 01:12:32.457
Hey. Nice party, huh, pal?

01:12:32.541 --> 01:12:34.125
Sure is, buddy.

01:12:34.208 --> 01:12:36.291
But I thought
you were playing Santa Claus.

01:12:36.375 --> 01:12:38.792
Me? Oh, no,
I leave that to the professionals.

01:12:38.875 --> 01:12:41.332
Jerry's been a mall Santa
ever since he retired.

01:12:41.832 --> 01:12:43.457
That a problem, Pete?

01:12:43.541 --> 01:12:44.750
Why would that be a problem?

01:12:44.832 --> 01:12:46.083
Just asking.

01:12:47.000 --> 01:12:50.250
Hey, you want to get me
one of those sodas over there?

01:12:53.832 --> 01:12:55.042
Thanks, kiddo.

01:12:56.582 --> 01:12:58.167
Kid's up to something.
I can feel it.

01:13:02.291 --> 01:13:03.832
Probably just a coincidence.

01:13:07.167 --> 01:13:08.291
Ho, ho, ho!

01:13:08.750 --> 01:13:10.167
And what's your name?

01:13:10.250 --> 01:13:11.667
Let me guess.

01:13:11.750 --> 01:13:13.750
It wasn't a name
20 years ago.

01:13:13.832 --> 01:13:15.332
- Am I right?
- Peter?

01:13:15.792 --> 01:13:17.707
- Dad, what's up?
- You know where Mia is?

01:13:17.792 --> 01:13:19.375
She's supposed to help me
with the hot dogs.

01:13:19.457 --> 01:13:20.667
Nope.

01:13:20.750 --> 01:13:22.042
Well, hey, come on.
I could use your help.

01:13:31.167 --> 01:13:32.875
Hey, Grandpa.

01:13:32.958 --> 01:13:34.958
What happened to you?
You're all wet.

01:13:35.375 --> 01:13:37.667
Some questions don't have answers, Pete.

01:13:37.750 --> 01:13:39.500
Hey, cookie?

01:13:39.875 --> 01:13:41.542
- No, it's okay.
- Oh, they're delicious.

01:13:41.625 --> 01:13:43.875
- No, it's really fine.
- Especially this one.

01:13:44.250 --> 01:13:45.958
- I'm good.
- You sure?

01:13:46.042 --> 01:13:47.582
I'm sure.

01:13:49.291 --> 01:13:51.042
Want to help me get some
mustard and ketchup on these

01:13:51.125 --> 01:13:53.083
bad boys and get 'em out to
the kids before they get cold?

01:13:53.375 --> 01:13:54.707
Sounds good, Dad.

01:13:54.792 --> 01:13:56.416
I'll do the front row,
you do the back?

01:13:56.832 --> 01:13:58.332
You're the boss.

01:14:01.457 --> 01:14:03.917
I'm so sorry.
That just slipped.

01:14:05.083 --> 01:14:06.833
I swear,
I didn't mean to do that.

01:14:08.083 --> 01:14:09.542
What are you gonna do?

01:14:11.875 --> 01:14:13.166
Oh, darn.

01:14:13.250 --> 01:14:14.917
Bottles must be overly full.

01:14:15.416 --> 01:14:18.166
Hey, Dad? The Christmas lights
are on the fritz again.

01:14:18.250 --> 01:14:21.000
- Could you check on them?
- I'm on it.

01:14:21.083 --> 01:14:24.000
Yeah, and, Peter, check on the air pump
for the bouncy house.

01:14:24.083 --> 01:14:26.291
Could be a little bit... bouncier.

01:14:50.750 --> 01:14:52.375
What the heck
is he up to now?

01:15:02.542 --> 01:15:04.582
Grandpa!

01:15:04.667 --> 01:15:06.792
Dad! Dad!

01:15:08.291 --> 01:15:09.833
Dad?

01:15:09.917 --> 01:15:11.582
Are you all right?

01:15:14.083 --> 01:15:16.375
I'm okay.
Found a quarter in here.

01:15:18.500 --> 01:15:20.500
Peter, we said no pranks.

01:15:20.582 --> 01:15:22.792
We shook hands on it, man-to-man.
What happened?

01:15:22.875 --> 01:15:24.707
What are you talking about?

01:15:24.792 --> 01:15:26.750
Grandpa, I swear, I didn't do that.

01:15:27.375 --> 01:15:28.375
Whoa!

01:15:31.833 --> 01:15:33.667
Santa's dead!

01:15:35.082 --> 01:15:37.166
Okay.
I might have did that.

01:15:37.250 --> 01:15:38.792
That's not good.

01:15:42.291 --> 01:15:45.917
Danny, Ed, did you see that?

01:15:47.207 --> 01:15:48.582
Epic.

01:15:49.582 --> 01:15:50.958
Here comes Santa.

01:15:51.457 --> 01:15:53.250
Ho, ho, ho.

01:15:56.166 --> 01:15:57.875
- My franks.
- Jerry!

01:15:57.958 --> 01:15:59.958
- Jerry, you all right?
- What happened?

01:16:02.417 --> 01:16:03.542
Fire!

01:16:04.125 --> 01:16:05.792
Everybody get back!
I got this!

01:16:07.625 --> 01:16:09.375
- Dad, I'll get the hose.
- Okay.

01:16:10.000 --> 01:16:11.542
All right, pull the pin.
Got it.

01:16:12.457 --> 01:16:14.708
"Point away from face..."

01:16:15.375 --> 01:16:16.625
I'm blind!

01:16:18.000 --> 01:16:19.667
I'm blind!

01:16:21.125 --> 01:16:22.207
I got it.

01:16:23.417 --> 01:16:24.917
Grandpa, get out of the way!

01:16:35.792 --> 01:16:37.207
My Christmas tree.

01:16:38.542 --> 01:16:40.582
My Christmas birthday cake.

01:16:44.125 --> 01:16:45.833
Oh! What have we done?

01:17:02.917 --> 01:17:03.958
No, no, no, no!

01:17:10.375 --> 01:17:11.457
Peter!

01:17:18.875 --> 01:17:19.958
Hi, Mom.

01:17:20.041 --> 01:17:21.542
Mia?

01:17:21.625 --> 01:17:22.958
Russell!

01:17:25.291 --> 01:17:27.000
Don't you run away,
Russell!

01:17:28.625 --> 01:17:29.875
Nothing happened.

01:17:31.708 --> 01:17:33.082
Okay, this is not my fault.

01:17:35.500 --> 01:17:37.625
Little help? Anybody?

01:17:45.582 --> 01:17:48.166
That's a pretty good scrape there,
Mr. Marino.

01:17:48.250 --> 01:17:49.792
Yeah?
You should see the tree.

01:17:50.792 --> 01:17:52.166
Thank you.

01:17:54.667 --> 01:17:57.000
What? What? It's nothing.
I'll be all right.

01:17:57.082 --> 01:17:59.750
Sure, you'll be all right.
Dad's always all right.

01:17:59.833 --> 01:18:02.332
Doesn't need anyone's help
or love.

01:18:02.875 --> 01:18:04.125
Oh, Sally, please, come on.

01:18:04.207 --> 01:18:06.417
- You could've been killed, Dad.
- Come on.

01:18:06.500 --> 01:18:09.166
You're overdramatizing.
It was an accident. That's all.

01:18:09.250 --> 01:18:10.875
- An accident?
- Yeah.

01:18:10.957 --> 01:18:13.750
What, you think I don't know
about the war, Dad?

01:18:13.833 --> 01:18:16.417
Or should I say
"Senior Soldier"?

01:18:16.500 --> 01:18:17.708
Oh... That.

01:18:17.792 --> 01:18:19.125
What were you two thinking?

01:18:19.207 --> 01:18:21.292
Don't blame the kid, Sally.
Please.

01:18:21.375 --> 01:18:23.000
It's all on me.
I'm the grown-up here,

01:18:23.082 --> 01:18:24.792
- and I should know better.
- Yeah, you should've.

01:18:24.875 --> 01:18:26.792
I'm sorry. I just...
It got out of hand, and...

01:18:26.875 --> 01:18:28.792
I have the money
to pay for everything.

01:18:28.875 --> 01:18:32.417
And I'll take my crew,
and we'll fix everything the way it was.

01:18:32.500 --> 01:18:34.792
It's not about the house
or the money, Dad.

01:18:35.332 --> 01:18:38.250
If you hated living with us so much,
you just should've said it.

01:18:38.332 --> 01:18:40.250
I never said I hated living with you.

01:18:40.332 --> 01:18:41.916
Exactly.
I just said you never said it.

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:43.916
What I'm saying, I never said that.

01:18:44.000 --> 01:18:46.082
We clear that up, hopefully?

01:18:46.166 --> 01:18:49.332
No. Forget about
what you never said.

01:18:50.250 --> 01:18:52.041
The point is, I just thought

01:18:52.125 --> 01:18:55.000
when you came home with us,
you'd realize that we love you

01:18:55.082 --> 01:18:56.875
and you'd change your mind
about living alone.

01:18:56.957 --> 01:18:59.332
But, of course,
that didn't happen.

01:18:59.417 --> 01:19:01.625
You're just so hell-bent on...

01:19:03.792 --> 01:19:06.375
funning it up.

01:19:06.457 --> 01:19:09.166
- Are you okay, Grandpa?
- Yeah. Grandpa's fine.

01:19:09.250 --> 01:19:11.166
Listen, sweetheart,
I'm really sorry

01:19:11.250 --> 01:19:12.792
about what happened
at your birthday party.

01:19:12.875 --> 01:19:14.000
It's okay.

01:19:14.082 --> 01:19:16.125
I brought you something
to make you feel better.

01:19:16.207 --> 01:19:19.750
That's very nice, but I gave
that to you, remember?

01:19:19.833 --> 01:19:21.000
Don't you want it?

01:19:21.082 --> 01:19:23.125
I think you need it more.

01:19:23.207 --> 01:19:25.207
We can call it a loan.

01:19:25.750 --> 01:19:28.375
That's very adult of you,
sweetheart.

01:19:29.916 --> 01:19:31.667
You'll be able to
take him home soon.

01:19:31.750 --> 01:19:34.667
The doctor just needs
to review the X-rays.

01:19:35.125 --> 01:19:36.708
We'll be in the waiting room.

01:19:50.957 --> 01:19:52.250
Can I go see him now?

01:19:52.332 --> 01:19:54.916
No. It'll be a long time

01:19:55.000 --> 01:19:58.500
before we leave the two of you
alone together again, ever.

01:19:58.583 --> 01:19:59.832
Is he gonna be okay?

01:19:59.916 --> 01:20:01.625
He'll be fine.
You and Mia, on the other hand,

01:20:01.708 --> 01:20:03.041
that's a different story.

01:20:03.457 --> 01:20:05.292
You're both chor-rounded
for the next six months.

01:20:05.417 --> 01:20:07.667
Chor-rounded?
What does that even mean?

01:20:07.750 --> 01:20:10.708
Chores plus grounded,
times six months.

01:20:10.792 --> 01:20:12.167
- What?
- Yeah.

01:20:12.250 --> 01:20:14.500
- So, that's a whole lot of both, isn't it?
- Mmm-hmm.

01:20:14.792 --> 01:20:17.000
But I didn't even do half
of the stuff that Peter did.

01:20:17.082 --> 01:20:18.583
This is so not fair.

01:20:18.667 --> 01:20:20.332
Can I be chor-rounded, too?

01:20:20.417 --> 01:20:22.957
No, sweetie,
you don't have to be chor-rounded.

01:20:26.625 --> 01:20:27.625
Russell.

01:20:30.583 --> 01:20:33.125
- Don't you move a muscle.
- Wait.

01:20:34.082 --> 01:20:35.750
- Wait, Mom! Come on!
- Russell!

01:20:35.832 --> 01:20:37.667
Dad, can you think rationally about...

01:20:37.750 --> 01:20:39.875
- Russell!
- She said not to move.

01:20:40.167 --> 01:20:42.167
- Russell!
- Get away from me!

01:20:48.708 --> 01:20:51.041
Get back here, you coward!

01:20:52.125 --> 01:20:53.875
Punk!

01:20:53.957 --> 01:20:56.250
Okay, that's it.
Mom is certifiably insane.

01:20:56.332 --> 01:20:58.542
- I'm going out there.
- Whoa, whoa. Hold on.

01:20:59.250 --> 01:21:01.207
I know your mother.
She can handle this.

01:21:10.375 --> 01:21:12.458
You're not gonna slug me,
are you, Mrs. Decker?

01:21:14.417 --> 01:21:16.082
No.

01:21:21.832 --> 01:21:23.250
What's happening right now?

01:21:24.082 --> 01:21:25.625
What's happening right now is

01:21:25.708 --> 01:21:28.292
I'm not gonna lose two years
of my daughter, Russell.

01:21:29.000 --> 01:21:30.957
Come on, take it
before I change my mind.

01:21:34.875 --> 01:21:36.332
Come by the house tomorrow.

01:21:36.417 --> 01:21:37.832
- Really?
- Yep.

01:21:38.750 --> 01:21:40.417
And bring some work clothes.

01:21:40.500 --> 01:21:45.082
I've got this giant hole
in the second floor, needs fixing.

01:21:48.875 --> 01:21:50.250
Okay.

01:21:51.292 --> 01:21:52.500
How'd that go?

01:21:53.250 --> 01:21:54.500
Thanks a lot, Mom.

01:21:54.583 --> 01:21:55.957
I didn't hurt him.

01:21:56.375 --> 01:21:57.375
Mmm-hmm.

01:21:57.875 --> 01:22:00.167
Everything's gonna be all right.

01:22:00.625 --> 01:22:02.332
Let's go get Grandpa
and go home.

01:22:06.207 --> 01:22:09.542
Excuse me. Can you check on Mr. Marino,
see if he's ready to go?

01:22:09.625 --> 01:22:10.957
Oh, he left already.

01:22:11.583 --> 01:22:12.916
I thought you all left.

01:22:13.000 --> 01:22:14.625
